
<p class="lead">We will create a contact group in your gmail account called "YOURCHURCH.ccb" and
populate it with all of the individuals in your ccb site that have 'profile listing' enabled.</p>

<%= render partial: "easy_steps" %>

<p class="small">Contacts that we create will also be added to your <i>system</i> group "My Contacts" because this is the group that gmail uses when syncing contacts to phones.</p>
<p class="small">Only those contacts that we create will get updated.  If you already have an existing contact with the same name in another group, it will NOT be touched.  When a contact record is updated, it is completely overwritten-- so if you make changes to these contact records on your phone, those changes will be lost.  Instead, you should change them in ccb.</p>

<%= form_tag(connect_path, method: "get") do %>
  <div class="checkbox input-lg">
    <label>
      <%= check_box_tag('recur') %>
      <%= label_tag('recur', "Automatically keep contacts up to date on a daily basis") %>
    </label>
  </div>
<p></p>
  <%= button_tag("Step 1 - Let's Connect to your Gmail &nbsp; <i class='fa fa-chevron-right'></i><i class='fa fa-chevron-right'></i>".html_safe, 
    type: 'submit',
    class: 'btn btn-success btn-default btn-lg white-space-reset',
    data: { disable_with: "Redirecting... <i class='fa fa-spin fa-spinner'></i>".html_safe }) %>
<% end %>

<div>
<img class="pull-right martop20" src="https://www.positivessl.com/images-new/PositiveSSL_tl_white2.gif" alt="SSL Certificate" title="SSL Certificate" border="0" />
</div>